        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 4:39PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 439 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bells Valley, or near Goshen, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Goshen...
Millboro...
Bells Valley...
Brownsburg...
and Yost.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
